filters

Class Filter

  • java.lang.Object
    • filters.Filter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RelativeStrengthIndex

    public abstract class Filter
extends Object
    The Filter class is merely a helpful tool in building your own filter. It includes several useful functions that will facillitate TRDR communication and information processing.

    The Filter communicates with TRDR through a SocketInterface.

    Acceptable Message types from Filter -> TRDR: 

     <MultiOrder.socketString()>
 <FilterParam.socketString()>
 <SocketFail.socketString()>
 <SubscriptionParam.socketString()>
    Acceptable Message types from TRDR -> Filter: 
     <StockRecord.socketString()>
 <FilterRecord.socketString()>
 <FilterParam.socketString()>
    Future Work I would suggest having a SimpleFilter class that will have all the functions you would need for your most basic of filters.
